  [1m[38;5;252m## Summary[0m
  • Problem: [38;5;189m`senseaudio`[39m bundled plugin only has ASR; no TTS.
  • Why it matters: completes the round trip in the same plugin; SenseAudio's [38;5;189m`/v1/t2a_v2`[39m is solid TTS and pairs with
  the ASR added in #66943.
  • What changed: registers a [38;5;189m`speechProvider`[39m in [38;5;189m`extensions/senseaudio/`[39m. Synthesizes via [38;5;189m`/v1/t2a_v2`[39m, lists system
  voices via [38;5;189m`/v1/get_voice`[39m, transcodes MP3→opus for [38;5;189m`voice-note`[39m targets. Errors split into HTTP / [38;5;189m`base_resp.[39m
  [38;5;189mstatus_code`[39m / missing-audio buckets.
  • What did NOT change: no core code; ASR untouched; streaming, telephony, voice cloning, text-generated voices out
  of scope.

